  Total Kenya Ltd. (TKNL) ,  Total SA (FP) â€™s unit
in the East African nation, climbed for the first day in five
after saying full-year profit surged 90 percent as sales almost
doubled on the acquisition of Chevron  Kenya  Ltd. last year.  The stock climbed 25 cents, or 0.9 percent, to 28.25
shillings by the 3 p.m. close in the capital, Nairobi.  Net income climbed to 916.2 million shillings ($10.9
million) in the year through December from 482.6 million
shillings a year earlier, Total Kenya said in a statement
published in the Nairobi-based Daily Nation newspaper yesterday.
Sales jumped 92 percent to 79.2 billion shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
